The article is a statement from the President regarding Senate Republicans blocking an infrastructure bill. The President criticizes the Republicans for obstructing a bill that would boost the economy and create jobs. He points out that the bill was supported by independent economists and had common-sense proposals. Despite being fully paid for and having the support of the majority of Americans, all Senate Republicans voted against it. The President believes that Republicans are out of touch with the American people and calls for an explanation as to why they refuse to prioritize job creation and economic growth. He urges Republicans to put the country first and do their job of serving the American people. The President promises to continue working towards moving the country forward until Republicans take action.